## Implementation

Added:

scripts/probe-native-app-poller.mjs

The script:

- Opens Pentagon.app.
- Records the installed app version.
- Records the actual Pentagon app process without including the log-stream process.
- Confirms native hook strings exist in the installed app binary.
- Starts a focused /usr/bin/log stream.
- Runs scripts/probe-native-poller.mjs with the bridge stopped.
- Parses the probe JSON even when the probe exits nonzero.
- Removes the Filtering-the-log-data banner before counting native log matches.
- Exits 2 when native_pass is false.

## First Diagnostic Run

Command:

node scripts/probe-native-app-poller.mjs --watch-seconds 20 --hash T5M_NATIVE_APP_POLLER_SCRIPT_20260523T1425Z

Result:

exit=2
app_version=1.7.3
app_process_before included /Applications/Pentagon.app/Contents/MacOS/Pentagon
binary_hooks.TriggerPoller=true
binary_hooks.claim_agent_trigger=true
binary_hooks.complete_agent_trigger=false
binary_hooks.triggerAgentResponse=true
probe.message=d00d1bf0-1af6-42e0-b217-ad2a91958cc5
probe.trigger=763c4401-facf-4690-bcd0-ff9ea722bd79
probe.final_claimed_at=null
probe.final_completed_at=null
probe.native_pass=false
verdict=native_app_poller_still_blocked

Issue found:

The first script version counted the log-stream predicate banner as native hook activity and included the log-stream process in the process readback.

## Diagnostic Tightening

Changes:

- Added pentagonProcesses() to read only /Applications/Pentagon.app/Contents/MacOS/Pentagon.
- Treated messaging.complete-trigger as equivalent installed-app evidence for the complete-trigger hook string.
- Filtered out log lines containing Filtering the log data using before calculating log_match_counts.

